{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727750200,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fD5L1KZGYMYR86333ZPfO3xF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/static/skills/memclaw/SKILL.md","offset":44,"limit":25},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/static/skills/memclaw/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n44: Reserve deletes (soft-delete, requires trust 3) for correcting genuinely\n45: wrong data.\n46: \n47: ## Trust levels\n48: \n49: Auto-registered at trust 1 on your first write.\n50: \n51: | Level | Name        | Read                      | Write                  |\n52: |:-----:|-------------|---------------------------|------------------------|\n53: | 0     | restricted  | —                         | —                      |\n54: | 1     | standard    | own fleet                 | own fleet              |\n55: | 2     | cross-fleet | all fleets in your tenant | own fleet              |\n56: | 3     | admin       | all                       | all, including deletes |\n57: \n58: Scope-based escalation:\n59: - browsing or reflecting with `scope=\"fleet\"` / `\"all\"` → trust 2\n60: - reporting outcomes (`memclaw_evolve`) at `scope=\"fleet\"` / `\"all\"` → trust 2 (default `scope=\"agent\"` needs only trust 1)\n61: - authoring your OWN `scope=agent` keystone (`memclaw_keystones_set`) → trust 1\n62: - authoring `scope=fleet` / `scope=tenant` / another agent's keystone → trust 2\n63: - `memclaw_manage op=delete` → trust 3\n64: \n65: If denied, surface the error; do not silently retry with a narrower scope.\n66: \n67: ## Sharing: visibility and scope\n68: \n\n(Showing lines 44-68 of 299. Use offset=69 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Reserve deletes (soft-delete, requires trust 3) for correcting genuinely\nwrong data.\n\n## Trust levels\n\nAuto-registered at trust 1 on your first write.\n\n| Level | Name        | Read                      | Write                  |\n|:-----:|-------------|---------------------------|------------------------|\n| 0     | restricted  | —                         | —                      |\n| 1     | standard    | own fleet                 | own fleet              |\n| 2     | cross-fleet | all fleets in your tenant | own fleet              |\n| 3     | admin       | all                       | all, including deletes |\n\nScope-based escalation:\n- browsing or reflecting with `scope=\"fleet\"` / `\"all\"` → trust 2\n- reporting outcomes (`memclaw_evolve`) at `scope=\"fleet\"` / `\"all\"` → trust 2 (default `scope=\"agent\"` needs only trust 1)\n- authoring your OWN `scope=agent` keystone (`memclaw_keystones_set`) → trust 1\n- authoring `scope=fleet` / `scope=tenant` / another agent's keystone → trust 2\n- `memclaw_manage op=delete` → trust 3","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/static/skills/memclaw/SKILL.md","text":"Reserve deletes (soft-delete, requires trust 3) for correcting genuinely\nwrong data.\n\n## Trust levels\n\nAuto-registered at trust 1 on your first write.\n\n| Level | Name        | Read                      | Write                  |\n|:-----:|-------------|---------------------------|------------------------|\n| 0     | restricted  | —                         | —                      |\n| 1     | standard    | own fleet                 | own fleet              |\n| 2     | cross-fleet | all fleets in your tenant | own fleet              |\n| 3     | admin       | all                       | all, including deletes |\n\nScope-based escalation:\n- browsing or reflecting with `scope=\"fleet\"` / `\"all\"` → trust 2\n- reporting outcomes (`memclaw_evolve`) at `scope=\"fleet\"` / `\"all\"` → trust 2 (default `scope=\"agent\"` needs only trust 1)\n- authoring your OWN `scope=agent` keystone (`memclaw_keystones_set`) → trust 1\n- authoring `scope=fleet` / `scope=tenant` / another agent's keystone → trust 2\n- `memclaw_manage op=delete` → trust 3\n\nIf denied, surface the error; do not silently retry with a narrower scope.\n\n## Sharing: visibility and scope\n","lineStart":44,"lineEnd":68,"totalLines":299,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/static/skills/memclaw/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1780727750189,"end":1780727750198}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f2e1af9b738ac0d016a23bfc609ac8191a5602663143d955c"}},"id":"prt_e9ba51e2c001emX9618TiDQSgF","sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","messageID":"msg_e9ba4e37f001oNc0rJNid6kXl0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727750200,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Uq2zElv3HXW1meGAo8fCl8Lh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/settings.py","offset":1,"limit":110},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/settings.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Per-tenant settings endpoints.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, Header, HTTPException\n4: from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession\n5: \n6: from core_api.auth import AuthContext, get_auth_context\n7: from core_api.db.session import get_db\n8: from core_api.services.organization_settings import (\n9:     PROVIDER_OPTIONS,\n10:     get_settings_for_display,\n11:     update_settings,\n12: )\n13: \n14: router = APIRouter(tags=[\"Auth & Account\"])\n15: \n16: \n17: def _resolve_tenant(auth: AuthContext, tenant_id: str | None) -> str:\n18:     \"\"\"Admin (tenant_id=None) can specify any tenant. Tenant users use their own.\"\"\"\n19:     is_admin = auth.tenant_id is None and not auth.is_demo\n20:     if is_admin and tenant_id:\n21:         return tenant_id\n22:     if auth.tenant_id:\n23:         return auth.tenant_id\n24:     raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail=\"tenant_id required\")\n25: \n26: \n27: @router.get(\"/settings\")\n28: async def get_tenant_settings(\n29:     tenant_id: str | None = None,\n30:     db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db),\n31:     auth: AuthContext = Depends(get_auth_context),\n32: ):\n33:     \"\"\"Get tenant settings (API keys masked). Admin can query any tenant.\"\"\"\n34:     tid = _resolve_tenant(auth, tenant_id)\n35:     return await get_settings_for_display(db, tid)\n36: \n37: \n38: @router.put(\"/settings\")\n39: async def update_tenant_settings(\n40:     body: dict,\n41:     tenant_id: str | None = None,\n42:     x_changed_by: str | None = Header(default=None, alias=\"X-Changed-By\"),\n43:     db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db),\n44:     auth: AuthContext = Depends(get_auth_context),\n45: ):\n46:     \"\"\"Update tenant settings. Accepts partial updates. API keys are encrypted at rest.\n47: \n48:     Audit attribution: honours ``X-Changed-By`` only when the caller is\n49:     authenticated via the admin API key (i.e. the enterprise admin-api proxy).\n50:     Regular user requests always use ``auth.user_id`` regardless of the header.\n51:     \"\"\"\n52:     tid = _resolve_tenant(auth, tenant_id)\n53:     if auth.is_demo:\n54:         raise HTTPException(status_code=403, detail=\"Demo sandbox is read-only\")\n55:     # Tenant settings include security-relevant toggles (e.g. require_agent_approval,\n56:     # which governs whether new agents start quarantined). An agent-scoped\n57:     # credential must not be able to flip them.\n58:     auth.enforce_not_agent_credential(\"change tenant settings\")\n59:     # Only trust X-Changed-By from admin-key callers (the enterprise proxy).\n60:     # Regular users could forge this header otherwise.\n61:     changed_by: str | None\n62:     if x_changed_by and auth.is_admin:\n63:         changed_by = x_changed_by\n64:     else:\n65:         changed_by = auth.user_id\n66:     # StandaloneTenantMiddleware injects tenant_id into the JSON body — strip it\n67:     # so the allowlist check in update_settings doesn't reject it.\n68:     body.pop(\"tenant_id\", None)\n69:     try:\n70:         return await update_settings(db, tid, body, changed_by=changed_by)\n71:     except ValueError as e:\n72:         raise HTTPException(status_code=422, detail=str(e)) from e\n73: \n74: \n75: @router.get(\"/settings/providers\")\n76: async def list_providers():\n77:     \"\"\"List available LLM providers and models for each function.\"\"\"\n78:     return PROVIDER_OPTIONS\n\n(End of file - total 78 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Per-tenant settings endpoints.\"\"\"\n\nfrom fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, Header, HTTPException\nfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession\n\nfrom core_api.auth import AuthContext, get_auth_context\nfrom core_api.db.session import get_db\nfrom core_api.services.organization_settings import (\n    PROVIDER_OPTIONS,\n    get_settings_for_display,\n    update_settings,\n)\n\nrouter = APIRouter(tags=[\"Auth & Account\"])\n\n\ndef _resolve_tenant(auth: AuthContext, tenant_id: str | None) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Admin (tenant_id=None) can specify any tenant. Tenant users use their own.\"\"\"\n    is_admin = auth.tenant_id is None and not auth.is_demo\n    if is_admin and tenant_id:","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/settings.py","text":"\"\"\"Per-tenant settings endpoints.\"\"\"\n\nfrom fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, Header, HTTPException\nfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession\n\nfrom core_api.auth import AuthContext, get_auth_context\nfrom core_api.db.session import get_db\nfrom core_api.services.organization_settings import (\n    PROVIDER_OPTIONS,\n    get_settings_for_display,\n    update_settings,\n)\n\nrouter = APIRouter(tags=[\"Auth & Account\"])\n\n\ndef _resolve_tenant(auth: AuthContext, tenant_id: str | None) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Admin (tenant_id=None) can specify any tenant. Tenant users use their own.\"\"\"\n    is_admin = auth.tenant_id is None and not auth.is_demo\n    if is_admin and tenant_id:\n        return tenant_id\n    if auth.tenant_id:\n        return auth.tenant_id\n    raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail=\"tenant_id required\")\n\n\n@router.get(\"/settings\")\nasync def get_tenant_settings(\n    tenant_id: str | None = None,\n    db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db),\n    auth: AuthContext = Depends(get_auth_context),\n):\n    \"\"\"Get tenant settings (API keys masked). Admin can query any tenant.\"\"\"\n    tid = _resolve_tenant(auth, tenant_id)\n    return await get_settings_for_display(db, tid)\n\n\n@router.put(\"/settings\")\nasync def update_tenant_settings(\n    body: dict,\n    tenant_id: str | None = None,\n    x_changed_by: str | None = Header(default=None, alias=\"X-Changed-By\"),\n    db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db),\n    auth: AuthContext = Depends(get_auth_context),\n):\n    \"\"\"Update tenant settings. Accepts partial updates. API keys are encrypted at rest.\n\n    Audit attribution: honours ``X-Changed-By`` only when the caller is\n    authenticated via the admin API key (i.e. the enterprise admin-api proxy).\n    Regular user requests always use ``auth.user_id`` regardless of the header.\n    \"\"\"\n    tid = _resolve_tenant(auth, tenant_id)\n    if auth.is_demo:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=403, detail=\"Demo sandbox is read-only\")\n    # Tenant settings include security-relevant toggles (e.g. require_agent_approval,\n    # which governs whether new agents start quarantined). An agent-scoped\n    # credential must not be able to flip them.\n    auth.enforce_not_agent_credential(\"change tenant settings\")\n    # Only trust X-Changed-By from admin-key callers (the enterprise proxy).\n    # Regular users could forge this header otherwise.\n    changed_by: str | None\n    if x_changed_by and auth.is_admin:\n        changed_by = x_changed_by\n    else:\n        changed_by = auth.user_id\n    # StandaloneTenantMiddleware injects tenant_id into the JSON body — strip it\n    # so the allowlist check in update_settings doesn't reject it.\n    body.pop(\"tenant_id\", None)\n    try:\n        return await update_settings(db, tid, body, changed_by=changed_by)\n    except ValueError as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=422, detail=str(e)) from e\n\n\n@router.get(\"/settings/providers\")\nasync def list_providers():\n    \"\"\"List available LLM providers and models for each function.\"\"\"\n    return PROVIDER_OPTIONS","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":78,"totalLines":78,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/settings.py","time":{"start":1780727750175,"end":1780727750199}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f2e1af9b738ac0d016a23bfc6099c8191bdb1c2d6b7d96957"}},"id":"prt_e9ba51e160015iJJle044LN1Zh","sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","messageID":"msg_e9ba4e37f001oNc0rJNid6kXl0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727750205,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_zJzkizNuzkcmu23NcABBdCX3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/memories.py","offset":1740,"limit":85},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/memories.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1740:     body: RedistributeRequest,\n1741:     tenant_id: str = Query(...),\n1742:     agent_id: str = Query(..., description=\"Requesting agent (must be trust_level >= 3)\"),\n1743:     auth: AuthContext = Depends(get_auth_context),\n1744:     db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db),\n1745: ):\n1746:     \"\"\"Bulk-reassign memories to a different agent.\n1747: \n1748:     Admin-only (trust_level >= 3).  Moves memories to ``target_agent_id``,\n1749:     auto-promoting ``scope_agent`` → ``scope_team`` to prevent data loss.\n1750: \n1751:     Cross-fleet moves are intentionally allowed — a primary use case is\n1752:     reassigning memories from a central orchestrator to domain specialists\n1753:     that may reside in different fleets.  The admin trust-level requirement\n1754:     (>= 3) is the authorization gate instead of fleet scoping.\n1755:     \"\"\"\n1756:     t0 = time.perf_counter()\n1757: \n1758:     auth.enforce_read_only()\n1759:     auth.enforce_usage_limits()\n1760:     auth.enforce_tenant(tenant_id)\n1761: \n1762:     # Verify requesting agent is admin\n1763:     caller = await lookup_agent(db, tenant_id, agent_id)\n1764:     if caller is None or caller.get(\"trust_level\", 0) < 3:\n1765:         raise HTTPException(\n1766:             status_code=403,\n1767:             detail=f\"Agent '{agent_id}' requires trust_level >= 3 for redistribute.\",\n1768:         )\n1769: \n1770:     # Verify target agent exists and is not restricted\n1771:     target = await lookup_agent(db, tenant_id, body.target_agent_id)\n1772:     if target is None:\n1773:         raise HTTPException(\n1774:             status_code=404,\n1775:             detail=f\"Target agent '{body.target_agent_id}' not found in tenant '{tenant_id}'.\",\n1776:         )\n1777:     if target.get(\"trust_level\", 0) < 1:\n1778:         raise HTTPException(\n1779:             status_code=403,\n1780:             detail=f\"Target agent '{body.target_agent_id}' is restricted (trust_level=0). \"\n1781:             \"Cannot assign memories to a restricted agent.\",\n1782:         )\n1783: \n1784:     # Usage quota\n1785:     if auth.tenant_id:  # skip usage metering for admin tokens\n1786:         await bulk_check_and_increment(db, tenant_id, len(body.memory_ids))\n1787: \n1788:     # Fetch matching memories (tenant-scoped, not deleted)\n1789:     stmt = select(Memory).where(\n1790:         Memory.id.in_(body.memory_ids),\n1791:         Memory.tenant_id == tenant_id,\n1792:         Memory.deleted_at.is_(None),\n1793:     )\n1794:     result = await db.execute(stmt)\n1795:     memories = result.scalars().all()\n1796: \n1797:     # Track IDs not found (deleted, wrong tenant, or non-existent)\n1798:     found_ids = {mem.id for mem in memories}\n1799:     not_found = [str(mid) for mid in body.memory_ids if mid not in found_ids]\n1800: \n1801:     moved = 0\n1802:     promoted = 0\n1803:     skipped = 0\n1804:     from_agents: set[str] = set()\n1805: \n1806:     for mem in memories:\n1807:         if mem.agent_id == body.target_agent_id:\n1808:             skipped += 1\n1809:             continue\n1810: \n1811:         from_agents.add(mem.agent_id)\n1812:         mem.agent_id = body.target_agent_id\n1813: \n1814:         # Auto-promote scope_agent to scope_team to prevent data loss\n1815:         if mem.visibility == \"scope_agent\":\n1816:             mem.visibility = \"scope_team\"\n1817:             promoted += 1\n1818: \n1819:         moved += 1\n1820: \n1821:     # Audit log (same transaction as memory mutations — single atomic commit)\n1822:     await log_action(\n1823:         db,\n1824:         tenant_id=tenant_id,\n\n(Showing lines 1740-1824 of 2023. Use offset=1825 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    body: RedistributeRequest,\n    tenant_id: str = Query(...),\n    agent_id: str = Query(..., description=\"Requesting agent (must be trust_level >= 3)\"),\n    auth: AuthContext = Depends(get_auth_context),\n    db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db),\n):\n    \"\"\"Bulk-reassign memories to a different agent.\n\n    Admin-only (trust_level >= 3).  Moves memories to ``target_agent_id``,\n    auto-promoting ``scope_agent`` → ``scope_team`` to prevent data loss.\n\n    Cross-fleet moves are intentionally allowed — a primary use case is\n    reassigning memories from a central orchestrator to domain specialists\n    that may reside in different fleets.  The admin trust-level requirement\n    (>= 3) is the authorization gate instead of fleet scoping.\n    \"\"\"\n    t0 = time.perf_counter()\n\n    auth.enforce_read_only()\n    auth.enforce_usage_limits()","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/memories.py","text":"    body: RedistributeRequest,\n    tenant_id: str = Query(...),\n    agent_id: str = Query(..., description=\"Requesting agent (must be trust_level >= 3)\"),\n    auth: AuthContext = Depends(get_auth_context),\n    db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db),\n):\n    \"\"\"Bulk-reassign memories to a different agent.\n\n    Admin-only (trust_level >= 3).  Moves memories to ``target_agent_id``,\n    auto-promoting ``scope_agent`` → ``scope_team`` to prevent data loss.\n\n    Cross-fleet moves are intentionally allowed — a primary use case is\n    reassigning memories from a central orchestrator to domain specialists\n    that may reside in different fleets.  The admin trust-level requirement\n    (>= 3) is the authorization gate instead of fleet scoping.\n    \"\"\"\n    t0 = time.perf_counter()\n\n    auth.enforce_read_only()\n    auth.enforce_usage_limits()\n    auth.enforce_tenant(tenant_id)\n\n    # Verify requesting agent is admin\n    caller = await lookup_agent(db, tenant_id, agent_id)\n    if caller is None or caller.get(\"trust_level\", 0) < 3:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=403,\n            detail=f\"Agent '{agent_id}' requires trust_level >= 3 for redistribute.\",\n        )\n\n    # Verify target agent exists and is not restricted\n    target = await lookup_agent(db, tenant_id, body.target_agent_id)\n    if target is None:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=404,\n            detail=f\"Target agent '{body.target_agent_id}' not found in tenant '{tenant_id}'.\",\n        )\n    if target.get(\"trust_level\", 0) < 1:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=403,\n            detail=f\"Target agent '{body.target_agent_id}' is restricted (trust_level=0). \"\n            \"Cannot assign memories to a restricted agent.\",\n        )\n\n    # Usage quota\n    if auth.tenant_id:  # skip usage metering for admin tokens\n        await bulk_check_and_increment(db, tenant_id, len(body.memory_ids))\n\n    # Fetch matching memories (tenant-scoped, not deleted)\n    stmt = select(Memory).where(\n        Memory.id.in_(body.memory_ids),\n        Memory.tenant_id == tenant_id,\n        Memory.deleted_at.is_(None),\n    )\n    result = await db.execute(stmt)\n    memories = result.scalars().all()\n\n    # Track IDs not found (deleted, wrong tenant, or non-existent)\n    found_ids = {mem.id for mem in memories}\n    not_found = [str(mid) for mid in body.memory_ids if mid not in found_ids]\n\n    moved = 0\n    promoted = 0\n    skipped = 0\n    from_agents: set[str] = set()\n\n    for mem in memories:\n        if mem.agent_id == body.target_agent_id:\n            skipped += 1\n            continue\n\n        from_agents.add(mem.agent_id)\n        mem.agent_id = body.target_agent_id\n\n        # Auto-promote scope_agent to scope_team to prevent data loss\n        if mem.visibility == \"scope_agent\":\n            mem.visibility = \"scope_team\"\n            promoted += 1\n\n        moved += 1\n\n    # Audit log (same transaction as memory mutations — single atomic commit)\n    await log_action(\n        db,\n        tenant_id=tenant_id,","lineStart":1740,"lineEnd":1824,"totalLines":2023,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/memories.py","time":{"start":1780727750185,"end":1780727750205}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f2e1af9b738ac0d016a23bfc609a0819183994304e2dc0584"}},"id":"prt_e9ba51e21001IIUlzF23fWYrK0","sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","messageID":"msg_e9ba4e37f001oNc0rJNid6kXl0"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780727750547,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","part":{"id":"prt_e9ba51f91001W4DmPBzbSos7Bq","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"","messageID":"msg_e9ba4e37f001oNc0rJNid6kXl0","sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":106025,"input":8561,"output":676,"reasoning":20,"cache":{"write":0,"read":96768}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780727752602,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","part":{"id":"prt_e9ba52791001Gni6bLw0HbUnLl","messageID":"msg_e9ba520d900100h0muaP70PmVp","sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","snapshot":"685fa0c54243913f462be42b55f44e02db09cfb6","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727755017,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_I9cYfg7FlOciIGXD7VFNJZ4Y","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/static/skills/memclaw/SKILL.md","offset":67,"limit":55},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/static/skills/memclaw/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n67: ## Sharing: visibility and scope\n68: \n69: **Visibility (on write):** `scope_agent` (private) · `scope_team`\n70: *(default — your fleet)* · `scope_org` (all fleets in tenant).\n71: \n72: **Scope (on read — `_list` / `_insights`):** `agent` *(default)* ·\n73: `fleet` (trust 2) · `all` (trust 2).\n74: \n75: Prefer `scope_team` when writing; prefer `scope=agent` when reading\n76: unless you need cross-agent context.\n77: \n78: ## Containers\n79: \n80: - **Memory** — unstructured, findable semantically. Decisions, observations, rules, outcomes, recaps.\n81: - **Doc** — structured record with a natural key (`collection + doc_id`). Customers, configs, task lists, inventories.\n82: - **Entity** — named graph object (person, project, service). Fetch by UUID from a prior recall.\n83: \n84: If you need semantic search, it's a memory. If you need keyed lookup,\n85: it's a doc. If you already hold an ID, it's an entity.\n86: \n87: **Cross-store discovery.** The memory and doc stores are not cross-searched.\n88: `memclaw_recall` never returns docs; `memclaw_doc` has no semantic query. If a\n89: doc needs to be findable by description — onboarding guides, fleet readmes,\n90: proposals others should discover — also write a short pointer memory whose\n91: content names the target (`collection`, `doc_id`) and describes it. A\n92: teammate's `memclaw_recall \"onboarding\"` then surfaces the pointer and their\n93: agent can `memclaw_doc op=read` the actual doc. Skip for docs only fetched\n94: by systems that already hold the id (caches, config).\n95: \n96: ## Good memories\n97: \n98: Dated, concrete, standalone, atomic, updated (not duplicated).\n99: \n100: ## Sharing skills\n101: \n102: Skills are SKILL.md artifacts that agents share across the fleet —\n103: debugging recipes, ops runbooks, refactor playbooks. They live as\n104: documents in the `skills` collection: discovery and sharing both go\n105: through `memclaw_doc`.\n106: \n107: ```\n108: # Discover\n109: memclaw_doc op=search collection=skills query=<natural language>\n110: memclaw_doc op=query  collection=skills              # browse by recency\n111: memclaw_doc op=read   collection=skills doc_id=<slug>  # full body\n112: \n113: # Share — slug is `[a-z0-9][a-z0-9._-]{0,99}` (filesystem-safe)\n114: memclaw_doc op=write collection=skills doc_id=<slug> \\\n115:   data={ \"name\": \"<slug>\", \"summary\": \"<one-liner>\", \"content\": \"<full SKILL.md>\" }\n116: \n117: # Remove\n118: memclaw_doc op=delete collection=skills doc_id=<slug>\n119: ```\n120: \n121: The `data[\"summary\"]` string (1-3 sentences, intent-focused) is what\n\n(Showing lines 67-121 of 299. Use offset=122 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## Sharing: visibility and scope\n\n**Visibility (on write):** `scope_agent` (private) · `scope_team`\n*(default — your fleet)* · `scope_org` (all fleets in tenant).\n\n**Scope (on read — `_list` / `_insights`):** `agent` *(default)* ·\n`fleet` (trust 2) · `all` (trust 2).\n\nPrefer `scope_team` when writing; prefer `scope=agent` when reading\nunless you need cross-agent context.\n\n## Containers\n\n- **Memory** — unstructured, findable semantically. Decisions, observations, rules, outcomes, recaps.\n- **Doc** — structured record with a natural key (`collection + doc_id`). Customers, configs, task lists, inventories.\n- **Entity** — named graph object (person, project, service). Fetch by UUID from a prior recall.\n\nIf you need semantic search, it's a memory. If you need keyed lookup,\nit's a doc. If you already hold an ID, it's an entity.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/static/skills/memclaw/SKILL.md","text":"## Sharing: visibility and scope\n\n**Visibility (on write):** `scope_agent` (private) · `scope_team`\n*(default — your fleet)* · `scope_org` (all fleets in tenant).\n\n**Scope (on read — `_list` / `_insights`):** `agent` *(default)* ·\n`fleet` (trust 2) · `all` (trust 2).\n\nPrefer `scope_team` when writing; prefer `scope=agent` when reading\nunless you need cross-agent context.\n\n## Containers\n\n- **Memory** — unstructured, findable semantically. Decisions, observations, rules, outcomes, recaps.\n- **Doc** — structured record with a natural key (`collection + doc_id`). Customers, configs, task lists, inventories.\n- **Entity** — named graph object (person, project, service). Fetch by UUID from a prior recall.\n\nIf you need semantic search, it's a memory. If you need keyed lookup,\nit's a doc. If you already hold an ID, it's an entity.\n\n**Cross-store discovery.** The memory and doc stores are not cross-searched.\n`memclaw_recall` never returns docs; `memclaw_doc` has no semantic query. If a\ndoc needs to be findable by description — onboarding guides, fleet readmes,\nproposals others should discover — also write a short pointer memory whose\ncontent names the target (`collection`, `doc_id`) and describes it. A\nteammate's `memclaw_recall \"onboarding\"` then surfaces the pointer and their\nagent can `memclaw_doc op=read` the actual doc. Skip for docs only fetched\nby systems that already hold the id (caches, config).\n\n## Good memories\n\nDated, concrete, standalone, atomic, updated (not duplicated).\n\n## Sharing skills\n\nSkills are SKILL.md artifacts that agents share across the fleet —\ndebugging recipes, ops runbooks, refactor playbooks. They live as\ndocuments in the `skills` collection: discovery and sharing both go\nthrough `memclaw_doc`.\n\n```\n# Discover\nmemclaw_doc op=search collection=skills query=<natural language>\nmemclaw_doc op=query  collection=skills              # browse by recency\nmemclaw_doc op=read   collection=skills doc_id=<slug>  # full body\n\n# Share — slug is `[a-z0-9][a-z0-9._-]{0,99}` (filesystem-safe)\nmemclaw_doc op=write collection=skills doc_id=<slug> \\\n  data={ \"name\": \"<slug>\", \"summary\": \"<one-liner>\", \"content\": \"<full SKILL.md>\" }\n\n# Remove\nmemclaw_doc op=delete collection=skills doc_id=<slug>\n```\n\nThe `data[\"summary\"]` string (1-3 sentences, intent-focused) is what","lineStart":67,"lineEnd":121,"totalLines":299,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/static/skills/memclaw/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1780727755009,"end":1780727755016}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_062e58bb54192106016a23bfc9d0588191951584990ef78a56"}},"id":"prt_e9ba52c68001Hn2oarwITDbVCu","sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","messageID":"msg_e9ba520d900100h0muaP70PmVp"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780727755310,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","part":{"id":"prt_e9ba5322c001QkfkEUpuv1QalW","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"7a8151d32c60a3f70441145d433ea4e7dd4b9ef6","messageID":"msg_e9ba520d900100h0muaP70PmVp","sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":111459,"input":6402,"output":82,"reasoning":15,"cache":{"write":0,"read":104960}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780727759680,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","part":{"id":"prt_e9ba5433f001r3cJYNs2s66iSB","messageID":"msg_e9ba53330001SrkwSNJCvgEy4U","sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","snapshot":"732429ead348ff5067b4a1e4e494cc60ac30b6e2","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727762733,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b3bOr5ne6GXY4OBzwhtvasTP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/organization_settings.py","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/organization_settings.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Per-organization settings — storage + resolution.\n2: \n3: Settings are stored as a JSONB blob in ``organization_settings`` (one row\n4: per organization, overrides only). Every update additionally writes a flat\n5: diff to ``organization_settings_audit`` for attribution and history.\n6: \n7: Resolution order for any value:\n8:     org override (cached) → global env default (``core_api.config.Settings``)\n9:     → hardcoded Pydantic default\n10: \n11: The function parameters here are still named ``tenant_id`` for call-site\n12: back-compat (CAURA-654) — the value is treated as the org-key internally.\n13: In OSS-standalone the tenant_id IS the org_id (single implicit org per\n14: tenant); in enterprise callers should pass the actual org_id (parameter\n15: rename to ``org_id`` is a follow-up that will touch ~20 call sites).\n16: \n17: Reads go through a per-process ``TTLCache`` (5-min TTL). Writes invalidate\n18: the local cache entry immediately; other workers catch up on TTL expiry.\n19: Cross-worker invalidation is tracked as a follow-up (see CAURA-571).\n20: \"\"\"\n21: \n22: from __future__ import annotations\n23: \n24: import logging\n25: from typing import Any\n26: \n27: from cachetools import TTLCache\n28: from croniter import CroniterBadCronError, croniter\n29: from sqlalchemy import func, select, text\n30: from sqlalchemy.dialects.postgresql import insert as pg_insert\n31: from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession\n32: \n33: from common.events.lifecycle_purge_request import (\n34:     MEMORY_RETENTION_MAX_DAYS,\n35:     MEMORY_RETENTION_MIN_DAYS,\n36: )\n37: from common.models.organization_settings import OrganizationSettings, OrganizationSettingsAudit\n38: from common.provider_names import ProviderName\n39: from core_api.config import settings as global_settings\n40: \n41: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n42: \n43: \n44: # ── Settings schema defaults ──\n45: \n46: DEFAULT_SETTINGS: dict = {\n47:     \"enrichment\": {\n48:         \"provider\": None,\n49:         \"model\": None,\n50:         \"enabled\": None,\n51:     },\n52:     \"recall\": {\n53:         \"provider\": None,\n54:         \"model\": None,\n55:         \"enabled\": None,\n56:     },\n57:     \"embedding\": {\n58:         \"provider\": None,\n59:         \"model\": None,\n60:     },\n61:     \"entity_extraction\": {\n62:         \"provider\": None,\n63:         \"model\": None,\n64:         \"enabled\": None,\n65:     },\n66:     \"fallback_llm\": {\n67:         \"provider\": None,\n68:         \"model\": None,\n69:     },\n70:     \"search\": {\n71:         \"recall_boost\": None,\n72:         \"graph_retrieval\": None,\n73:     },\n74:     \"crystallizer\": {\n75:         \"auto_crystallize\": None,\n76:     },\n77:     \"dedup\": {\n78:         \"semantic_dedup_enabled\": None,\n79:     },\n80:     \"lifecycle\": {\n81:         \"lifecycle_automation_enabled\": None,\n82:         # Days to keep soft-deleted memories before they're physically\n83:         # purged (CAURA-656). Daily cron reads this per-org and runs\n84:         # ``purge-soft-deleted``. ``None`` means \"use the global\n85:         # default\" (30 — see ResolvedConfig.memory_retention_days).\n86:         # Range constrained to 1-30 by the validator below; the UI\n87:         # numeric input mirrors that range.\n88:         \"memory_retention_days\": None,\n89:     },\n90:     \"entity_linking\": {\n91:         \"auto_entity_linking_enabled\": None,\n92:     },\n93:     # Periodic discovery insights (lifecycle-insights cron). Opt-in:\n94:     # default is False because each tick runs an LLM reasoning pass\n95:     # per fleet (or per tenant when fleet-less) and that cost is not\n96:     # justified for every corpus. An org flips this to True when it\n97:     # wants the daily ``generate_insights(focus='discover')`` pass.\n98:     # The activity gate inside the consumer additionally skips ticks\n99:     # where no non-insight memories have been written since the last\n100:     # insights run, so even an enabled tenant pays only when the\n101:     # corpus has grown.\n102:     \"insights\": {\n103:         \"auto_insights_enabled\": None,\n104:     },\n105:     \"chunking\": {\n106:         \"auto_chunk_enabled\": None,\n107:     },\n108:     \"write\": {\n109:         \"default_write_mode\": None,  # None = \"fast\"; \"fast\" | \"strong\"\n110:         # CAURA-123 — RDF triple emission. When true (the default), a\n111:         # pre-write step extracts (subject_entity_id, predicate,\n112:         # object_value) from the request so the deterministic RDF\n113:         # contradiction path (contradiction_detector.py) can fire\n114:         # instead of falling through to the LLM. ``None`` resolves to\n115:         # the global default (true).\n116:         \"triple_emission_enabled\": None,\n117:         # CAURA-130 (L3.8) — Path C retraction kill-switch. When true\n118:         # (the default), Path C's ``_attempt_path_c_retraction`` runs\n119:         # the entity-aware judge and may revert a Path A verdict. When\n120:         # false, Path C skips retraction entirely and Path A's verdict\n121:         # stands. Ops escape valve for tenants whose retraction\n122:         # misbehaves; flip per-tenant without a deploy.\n123:         \"retraction_enabled\": None,\n124:     },\n125:     \"agents\": {\n126:         \"require_agent_approval\": None,\n127:     },\n128:     # CAURA-444 — plugin auto-upgrade. When `auto_upgrade_enabled` is\n129:     # true (the default), the heartbeat handler queues a `deploy`\n130:     # command for any node whose `plugin_version` is older than\n131:     # `MIN_RECOMMENDED_PLUGIN_VERSION` (version_compat.py).\n132:     # Per-tenant flip allows operators to opt out.\n133:     #\n134:     # The `KNOWN_BROKEN_DEPLOY_VERSIONS` denylist (in routes/fleet.py)\n135:     # is a separate global guard that prevents auto-deploy specifically\n136:     # for plugin versions whose deploy machinery is itself broken\n137:     # (currently: 2.3.0 — drift in srcFiles + missing version-stamp).\n138:     \"memclaw\": {\n139:         \"auto_upgrade_enabled\": None,  # None = use global default (true)\n140:     },\n141:     \"security_audit\": {\n142:         \"schedule_enabled\": None,\n143:         \"schedule_cron\": None,\n144:         \"alerts_enabled\": None,\n145:         \"alert_recipients\": None,\n146:         \"alert_score_below\": None,\n147:         \"alert_critical_findings_min\": None,\n148:         \"alert_score_drop_delta\": None,\n149:     },\n150:     \"entity_blocklist\": [\n151:         \"team\",\n152:         \"meeting\",\n153:         \"project\",\n154:         \"system\",\n155:         \"process\",\n156:         \"approach\",\n157:         \"update\",\n158:         \"issue\",\n159:         \"change\",\n160:         \"result\",\n161:         \"group\",\n162:         \"company\",\n163:         \"person\",\n164:         \"user\",\n165:         \"client\",\n166:         \"thing\",\n167:         \"stuff\",\n168:         \"idea\",\n169:         \"work\",\n170:         \"code\",\n171:     ],\n172:     \"api_keys\": {},\n173: }\n174: \n175: # Keys are ``ProviderName`` enum values (.value) so a typo here is caught\n176: # at import time rather than silently producing an entry UI that no tenant\n177: # can select.\n178: PROVIDER_OPTIONS = {\n179:     \"enrichment\": {\n180:         ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"gpt-5.4-nano\", \"gpt-5.4-mini\", \"gpt-4.1-nano\", \"gpt-4o-mini\"],\n181:         ProviderName.GEMINI.value: [\n182:             \"gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview\",\n183:             \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\",\n184:             \"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n185:         ],\n186:     },\n187:     \"recall\": {\n188:         ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"gpt-5.4-nano\", \"gpt-5.4-mini\", \"gpt-4.1-nano\", \"gpt-4o-mini\"],\n189:         ProviderName.GEMINI.value: [\n190:             \"gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview\",\n191:             \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\",\n192:             \"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n193:         ],\n194:     },\n195:     \"embedding\": {\n196:         ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"text-embedding-3-small\", \"text-embedding-3-large\"],\n197:     },\n198:     \"entity_extraction\": {\n199:         ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"gpt-5.4-nano\", \"gpt-5.4-mini\", \"gpt-4.1-nano\", \"gpt-4o-mini\"],\n200:         ProviderName.GEMINI.value: [\n201:             \"gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview\",\n202:             \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\",\n203:             \"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n204:         ],\n205:     },\n206:     \"fallback_llm\": {\n207:         ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"gpt-5.4-nano\", \"gpt-5.4-mini\", \"gpt-4.1-nano\", \"gpt-4o-mini\"],\n208:         ProviderName.GEMINI.value: [\n209:             \"gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview\",\n210:             \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\",\n211:             \"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n212:         ],\n213:         ProviderName.ANTHROPIC.value: [\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"],\n214:         ProviderName.OPENROUTER.value: [\"openai/gpt-5.4-nano\", \"openai/gpt-4.1-nano\"],\n215:     },\n216: }\n217: \n218: \n219: def _remap_vertex(provider: str) -> str:\n220:     \"\"\"Remap deprecated tenant-tier ``vertex`` provider to ``openai``.\n221: \n222:     Existing tenants with ``provider=\"vertex\"`` saved in DB settings hit\n223:     ``ValueError`` on every LLM call after the tenant-tier removal.\n224:     ``call_with_fallback`` catches those but logs misleadingly and may\n225:     silently drop to FakeLLMProvider for GCP-only tenants. Remap at the\n226:     read-side so stored settings degrade gracefully.\n227:     \"\"\"\n228:     if provider == \"vertex\":\n229:         logger.warning(\n230:             \"Tenant has provider='vertex' in stored settings; \"\n231:             \"vertex is platform-tier only. Remapping to 'openai'.\"\n232:         )\n233:         return \"openai\"\n234:     return provider\n235: \n236: \n237: # ── TTL cache: org_id → settings dict ──\n238: #\n239: # Per-process cache; each uvicorn worker has its own. Staleness across workers\n240: # is bounded by the TTL (5 min). Writes on the current worker invalidate\n241: # locally; others catch up on expiry. See CAURA-571 for cross-worker NOTIFY.\n242: #\n243: # No locking: cache misses may issue duplicate DB reads under concurrency, but\n244: # the query is an indexed PK lookup and the result is identical, so racing\n245: # populations are harmless.\n246: _settings_cache: TTLCache[str, dict] = TTLCache(maxsize=10_000, ttl=300)\n247: \n248: \n249: def _deep_merge(old: Any, new: Any) -> Any:\n250:     \"\"\"Return ``old`` with ``new`` merged recursively for nested dicts.\n251: \n252:     Non-dict values in ``new`` overwrite ``old`` wholesale (including lists).\n253:     \"\"\"\n254:     if not isinstance(old, dict) or not isinstance(new, dict):\n255:         return new\n256:     out = dict(old)\n257:     for k, v in new.items():\n258:         if isinstance(v, dict) and isinstance(out.get(k), dict):\n259:             out[k] = _deep_merge(out[k], v)\n260:         else:\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 853. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Per-organization settings — storage + resolution.\n\nSettings are stored as a JSONB blob in ``organization_settings`` (one row\nper organization, overrides only). Every update additionally writes a flat\ndiff to ``organization_settings_audit`` for attribution and history.\n\nResolution order for any value:\n    org override (cached) → global env default (``core_api.config.Settings``)\n    → hardcoded Pydantic default\n\nThe function parameters here are still named ``tenant_id`` for call-site\nback-compat (CAURA-654) — the value is treated as the org-key internally.\nIn OSS-standalone the tenant_id IS the org_id (single implicit org per\ntenant); in enterprise callers should pass the actual org_id (parameter\nrename to ``org_id`` is a follow-up that will touch ~20 call sites).\n\nReads go through a per-process ``TTLCache`` (5-min TTL). Writes invalidate\nthe local cache entry immediately; other workers catch up on TTL expiry.\nCross-worker invalidation is tracked as a follow-up (see CAURA-571).\n\"\"\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/organization_settings.py","text":"\"\"\"Per-organization settings — storage + resolution.\n\nSettings are stored as a JSONB blob in ``organization_settings`` (one row\nper organization, overrides only). Every update additionally writes a flat\ndiff to ``organization_settings_audit`` for attribution and history.\n\nResolution order for any value:\n    org override (cached) → global env default (``core_api.config.Settings``)\n    → hardcoded Pydantic default\n\nThe function parameters here are still named ``tenant_id`` for call-site\nback-compat (CAURA-654) — the value is treated as the org-key internally.\nIn OSS-standalone the tenant_id IS the org_id (single implicit org per\ntenant); in enterprise callers should pass the actual org_id (parameter\nrename to ``org_id`` is a follow-up that will touch ~20 call sites).\n\nReads go through a per-process ``TTLCache`` (5-min TTL). Writes invalidate\nthe local cache entry immediately; other workers catch up on TTL expiry.\nCross-worker invalidation is tracked as a follow-up (see CAURA-571).\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom typing import Any\n\nfrom cachetools import TTLCache\nfrom croniter import CroniterBadCronError, croniter\nfrom sqlalchemy import func, select, text\nfrom sqlalchemy.dialects.postgresql import insert as pg_insert\nfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession\n\nfrom common.events.lifecycle_purge_request import (\n    MEMORY_RETENTION_MAX_DAYS,\n    MEMORY_RETENTION_MIN_DAYS,\n)\nfrom common.models.organization_settings import OrganizationSettings, OrganizationSettingsAudit\nfrom common.provider_names import ProviderName\nfrom core_api.config import settings as global_settings\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\n# ── Settings schema defaults ──\n\nDEFAULT_SETTINGS: dict = {\n    \"enrichment\": {\n        \"provider\": None,\n        \"model\": None,\n        \"enabled\": None,\n    },\n    \"recall\": {\n        \"provider\": None,\n        \"model\": None,\n        \"enabled\": None,\n    },\n    \"embedding\": {\n        \"provider\": None,\n        \"model\": None,\n    },\n    \"entity_extraction\": {\n        \"provider\": None,\n        \"model\": None,\n        \"enabled\": None,\n    },\n    \"fallback_llm\": {\n        \"provider\": None,\n        \"model\": None,\n    },\n    \"search\": {\n        \"recall_boost\": None,\n        \"graph_retrieval\": None,\n    },\n    \"crystallizer\": {\n        \"auto_crystallize\": None,\n    },\n    \"dedup\": {\n        \"semantic_dedup_enabled\": None,\n    },\n    \"lifecycle\": {\n        \"lifecycle_automation_enabled\": None,\n        # Days to keep soft-deleted memories before they're physically\n        # purged (CAURA-656). Daily cron reads this per-org and runs\n        # ``purge-soft-deleted``. ``None`` means \"use the global\n        # default\" (30 — see ResolvedConfig.memory_retention_days).\n        # Range constrained to 1-30 by the validator below; the UI\n        # numeric input mirrors that range.\n        \"memory_retention_days\": None,\n    },\n    \"entity_linking\": {\n        \"auto_entity_linking_enabled\": None,\n    },\n    # Periodic discovery insights (lifecycle-insights cron). Opt-in:\n    # default is False because each tick runs an LLM reasoning pass\n    # per fleet (or per tenant when fleet-less) and that cost is not\n    # justified for every corpus. An org flips this to True when it\n    # wants the daily ``generate_insights(focus='discover')`` pass.\n    # The activity gate inside the consumer additionally skips ticks\n    # where no non-insight memories have been written since the last\n    # insights run, so even an enabled tenant pays only when the\n    # corpus has grown.\n    \"insights\": {\n        \"auto_insights_enabled\": None,\n    },\n    \"chunking\": {\n        \"auto_chunk_enabled\": None,\n    },\n    \"write\": {\n        \"default_write_mode\": None,  # None = \"fast\"; \"fast\" | \"strong\"\n        # CAURA-123 — RDF triple emission. When true (the default), a\n        # pre-write step extracts (subject_entity_id, predicate,\n        # object_value) from the request so the deterministic RDF\n        # contradiction path (contradiction_detector.py) can fire\n        # instead of falling through to the LLM. ``None`` resolves to\n        # the global default (true).\n        \"triple_emission_enabled\": None,\n        # CAURA-130 (L3.8) — Path C retraction kill-switch. When true\n        # (the default), Path C's ``_attempt_path_c_retraction`` runs\n        # the entity-aware judge and may revert a Path A verdict. When\n        # false, Path C skips retraction entirely and Path A's verdict\n        # stands. Ops escape valve for tenants whose retraction\n        # misbehaves; flip per-tenant without a deploy.\n        \"retraction_enabled\": None,\n    },\n    \"agents\": {\n        \"require_agent_approval\": None,\n    },\n    # CAURA-444 — plugin auto-upgrade. When `auto_upgrade_enabled` is\n    # true (the default), the heartbeat handler queues a `deploy`\n    # command for any node whose `plugin_version` is older than\n    # `MIN_RECOMMENDED_PLUGIN_VERSION` (version_compat.py).\n    # Per-tenant flip allows operators to opt out.\n    #\n    # The `KNOWN_BROKEN_DEPLOY_VERSIONS` denylist (in routes/fleet.py)\n    # is a separate global guard that prevents auto-deploy specifically\n    # for plugin versions whose deploy machinery is itself broken\n    # (currently: 2.3.0 — drift in srcFiles + missing version-stamp).\n    \"memclaw\": {\n        \"auto_upgrade_enabled\": None,  # None = use global default (true)\n    },\n    \"security_audit\": {\n        \"schedule_enabled\": None,\n        \"schedule_cron\": None,\n        \"alerts_enabled\": None,\n        \"alert_recipients\": None,\n        \"alert_score_below\": None,\n        \"alert_critical_findings_min\": None,\n        \"alert_score_drop_delta\": None,\n    },\n    \"entity_blocklist\": [\n        \"team\",\n        \"meeting\",\n        \"project\",\n        \"system\",\n        \"process\",\n        \"approach\",\n        \"update\",\n        \"issue\",\n        \"change\",\n        \"result\",\n        \"group\",\n        \"company\",\n        \"person\",\n        \"user\",\n        \"client\",\n        \"thing\",\n        \"stuff\",\n        \"idea\",\n        \"work\",\n        \"code\",\n    ],\n    \"api_keys\": {},\n}\n\n# Keys are ``ProviderName`` enum values (.value) so a typo here is caught\n# at import time rather than silently producing an entry UI that no tenant\n# can select.\nPROVIDER_OPTIONS = {\n    \"enrichment\": {\n        ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"gpt-5.4-nano\", \"gpt-5.4-mini\", \"gpt-4.1-nano\", \"gpt-4o-mini\"],\n        ProviderName.GEMINI.value: [\n            \"gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview\",\n            \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\",\n            \"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n        ],\n    },\n    \"recall\": {\n        ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"gpt-5.4-nano\", \"gpt-5.4-mini\", \"gpt-4.1-nano\", \"gpt-4o-mini\"],\n        ProviderName.GEMINI.value: [\n            \"gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview\",\n            \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\",\n            \"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n        ],\n    },\n    \"embedding\": {\n        ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"text-embedding-3-small\", \"text-embedding-3-large\"],\n    },\n    \"entity_extraction\": {\n        ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"gpt-5.4-nano\", \"gpt-5.4-mini\", \"gpt-4.1-nano\", \"gpt-4o-mini\"],\n        ProviderName.GEMINI.value: [\n            \"gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview\",\n            \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\",\n            \"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n        ],\n    },\n    \"fallback_llm\": {\n        ProviderName.OPENAI.value: [\"gpt-5.4-nano\", \"gpt-5.4-mini\", \"gpt-4.1-nano\", \"gpt-4o-mini\"],\n        ProviderName.GEMINI.value: [\n            \"gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview\",\n            \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\",\n            \"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n        ],\n        ProviderName.ANTHROPIC.value: [\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"],\n        ProviderName.OPENROUTER.value: [\"openai/gpt-5.4-nano\", \"openai/gpt-4.1-nano\"],\n    },\n}\n\n\ndef _remap_vertex(provider: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Remap deprecated tenant-tier ``vertex`` provider to ``openai``.\n\n    Existing tenants with ``provider=\"vertex\"`` saved in DB settings hit\n    ``ValueError`` on every LLM call after the tenant-tier removal.\n    ``call_with_fallback`` catches those but logs misleadingly and may\n    silently drop to FakeLLMProvider for GCP-only tenants. Remap at the\n    read-side so stored settings degrade gracefully.\n    \"\"\"\n    if provider == \"vertex\":\n        logger.warning(\n            \"Tenant has provider='vertex' in stored settings; \"\n            \"vertex is platform-tier only. Remapping to 'openai'.\"\n        )\n        return \"openai\"\n    return provider\n\n\n# ── TTL cache: org_id → settings dict ──\n#\n# Per-process cache; each uvicorn worker has its own. Staleness across workers\n# is bounded by the TTL (5 min). Writes on the current worker invalidate\n# locally; others catch up on expiry. See CAURA-571 for cross-worker NOTIFY.\n#\n# No locking: cache misses may issue duplicate DB reads under concurrency, but\n# the query is an indexed PK lookup and the result is identical, so racing\n# populations are harmless.\n_settings_cache: TTLCache[str, dict] = TTLCache(maxsize=10_000, ttl=300)\n\n\ndef _deep_merge(old: Any, new: Any) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"Return ``old`` with ``new`` merged recursively for nested dicts.\n\n    Non-dict values in ``new`` overwrite ``old`` wholesale (including lists).\n    \"\"\"\n    if not isinstance(old, dict) or not isinstance(new, dict):\n        return new\n    out = dict(old)\n    for k, v in new.items():\n        if isinstance(v, dict) and isinstance(out.get(k), dict):\n            out[k] = _deep_merge(out[k], v)\n        else:","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":853,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/organization_settings.py","time":{"start":1780727762726,"end":1780727762732}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0afff1e68c41f3da016a23bfd160308191ac11de3cf6f9825b"}},"id":"prt_e9ba54a0b001wtWI3kmWutnUrp","sessionID":"ses_1645cad25ffe4Zj0121cwP5hrZ","messageID":"msg_e9ba53330001SrkwSNJCvgEy4U"}}
